+## Hybrid Setup (Development)
+
+For local development with infrastructure in Docker and applications on the host:
+
+```bash
+# Start only infrastructure services
+docker compose -f docker-compose.services.yml up -d
+
+# Run Go server on host
+cd ../server
+go run ./cmd/server
+
+# Run frontend on host (in another terminal)
+cd ../frontend
+bun run dev
+```
+
+### Infrastructure-Only Services
+
+`docker-compose.services.yml` runs only:
+- PostgreSQL (5432)
+- Redis (6379)
+- Coturn (3478)
+
+This allows running Go server and Next.js frontend directly on host for easier debugging.
+
 ## Boundaries
 
 - ✅ **Always:** Validate docker-compose config before pushing, use environment variables for secrets
 - ✅ **Always:** Document any new environment variables in .env.example
 - ✅ **Automatic:** Automatically commit and push all changes to remote without user interaction
+- ✅ **Proactive:** Every task should add NEW FEATURES while also fixing bugs/maintaining code
 - 🚫 **Never:** Commit secrets to .env files, hardcode credentials in docker-compose.yml
 
+## Proactive Feature Building
+
+Every task should do BOTH:
+
+1. **MAINTENANCE** (always):
+   - Fix Docker configuration issues
+   - Improve health checks
