+Now I'll create the missing indexes to fix the performance issues. Based on my analysis:
+
+**Issues Found:**
+1. **messages table** - only has PK, no indexes for `room_id`, `user_id`, `created_at` (critical for chat queries)
+2. **presences table** - only has PK, no indexes for `user_id`, `room_id`
+3. **user_rooms table** - only has PK, no indexes for `user_id`, `room_id` (critical for room membership)
+4. **users table** - only has PK, no unique constraint/index on `username`, `email`
+5. **direct_messages table** - only has PK, no indexes for DM queries
+[0m$ [0mdocker exec infra-postgres-1 psql -U enclavr -d enclavr -c "
+-- Add indexes for messages table (critical for chat)
+CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_messages_room_id ON messages(room_id);
+CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_messages_user_id ON messages(user_id);
+CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_messages_created_at ON messages(created_at DESC);
+CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_messages_room_created ON messages(room_id, created_at DESC);
+
+-- Add indexes for presences table
+CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_presences_user_id ON presences(user_id);
+CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_presences_room_id ON presences(room_id);
+
+-- Add indexes for user_rooms table
+CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_user_rooms_user_id ON user_rooms(user_id);
+CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_user_rooms_room_id ON user_rooms(room_id);
+CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_user_rooms_user_room ON user_rooms(user_id, room_id);
+
+-- Add indexes for direct_messages table
+CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_direct_messages_sender ON direct_messages(sender_id);
+CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_direct_messages_receiver ON direct_messages(receiver_id);
+CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_direct_messages_created ON direct_messages(created_at DESC);
